Operations : Old West Investment Management, LLC


























Business Operations
In the investment business, a majority of investment firm failures stem from operational shortcomings and not poor investment performance.  As such, Old West believes that we have an obligation to focus as much time and effort on our operational systems and processes as we do on analyzing the companies that we invest in.
The mission of Business Operations is to treat our clients as we ourselves would like to be treated; execute effectively and efficiently, report accurately and timely, and respect all clients equally. 
The purpose of Business Operations at Old West is three-fold:

Execute the investment strategy as determined by the Investment Team
Fulfill obligations for regulatory compliance
Develop and maintain client relationships

Our mission is to treat our clients as we ourselves would like to be treated; execute effectively and efficiently, report accurately and timely, and respect all clients equally.
What does this mean for our clients? It means that we will never put our own interests ahead of our clients’ and that no client is more important than another. It also means that we will create processes that minimize operational risk and place a focus on building out infrastructure designed to return timely and relevant information to our clients.
Old West Investment Management utilizes a straight through process that creates a seamless workflow from portfolio construction through trade settlement. Our integrated processes support our philosophy in putting clients’ interests first so that we can pass on lower overall costs and best execution. We do not make a market in securities and so we are not conflicted with how, when, and where we trade an account. In addition, we take pride in doing our own research, as noted within the Investment Process section, and will never support the costs of this research with soft-dollar arrangements.
In addition to the above, we also take pride in the information and materials we make available to our clients.  We tirelessly evaluate this information for usefulness and relevancy while continuing to explore new ways of getting information into the hands of our clients.  The result of this effort is a consolidated report package that we make available to our clients on a quarterly basis.
We demand the same of ourselves as we demand of the owner-managers we seek to invest in through our Investment Process, and ultimately would like to operate a company that we ourselves would deem worthy of investment if our shares were publicly traded.




























